{"name":"Luck","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>Many undiscovered psykers are known for their luck or good fortune. Such psykers might not even be aware of their own true nature, but subconsciously manipulate events through a variety of psychic effects, from telepathic hints to telekinetic nudges. Of course, if others knew the true reason for their ability to seemingly defy the odds, they would not consider these psykers fortunate, but damned&mdash;as might a psyker himself.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"gain a bonus to next action","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Perception 30","action":"Half","focusPower":{"difficulty":0,"test":"Awareness"},"range":"Self","sustained":"No","subtype":"Concentration","effect":"<p>If the Focus Power test is successful, the psyker gains a bonus of 5 plus his psy rating on the next test he attempts this round. If the psyker fails the Focus Power test by 2 or more degrees of failure, his misguided attempt to call on the Warp backires, and the resultant psychic ripples inlict a penalty equal to twice his psy rating on his next test this round.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/PsychicPowers/psychic-waves.svg","effects":[],"_id":"1V6Y3FcXv82iLgOu"}
{"name":"Aura of Fear","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>Summoning his eldritch powers, the psyker projects a fearful aura. All those who witness him see their own deepest fears projected onto the psyker, not with their eyes, but in their minds.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"gains the Fear (1) trait","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Fellowship 35, 5+ Insanity points","action":"Full","focusPower":{"difficulty":-20,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"Self","sustained":"Half Action","subtype":"Concentration","effect":"<p>The psyker gains the Fear (1) trait as long as he sustains this power.</p>\n<p>Psychic Phenomena: Instead of rolling for Psychic Phenomena should the situation call for it, the psyker instead must take a Fear (4) test and also suffer Warp Shock as per page 289 of the DARK HERESY Core Rulebook if he fails.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/PsychicPowers/psychic-waves.svg","effects":[],"_id":"3k3ilM3hPgKZB7ji"}
{"name":"Suggestion","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>Although a far cry from the mind-inluencing techniques of a trained telepath, many wyrds and nascent psykers possess a preternatural ability to convince others of small falsehoods. As with many of the powers such psykers evince, this is a useful survival mechanism, allowing the psyker to evade detection.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"convince others of small falsehoods","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Rank 1 (Known) in the Deceive skill","action":"Full","focusPower":{"difficulty":-10,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"1*PR","sustained":"No","subtype":"Concentration","effect":"<p>The psyker convinces the target of a small, but potentially important lie. The target opposes this with a Challenging (+0) Willpower test, which the GM should modify based on the credibility and scope of the lie. In the case of clearly impossible lies, the target succeeds automatically (scoring 1 more degree of success than the psyker). For instance, a human psyker might suggest that a guard has already checked his identification, but would have no possibility of convincing that same guard that the psyker is a Space Marine.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/PsychicPowers/psychic-waves.svg","effects":[],"_id":"D3SSzahtd2ahW3jd"}
{"name":"Ignite","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>The psyker draws upon his anger, whether knowingly or not, and channels the Warp to produce a physical manifestation of his burning rage.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Illuminate roughly 5m","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Willpower 30","action":"Half","focusPower":{"difficulty":0,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"5m x PR","sustained":"Half","subtype":"Attack, Concentration","effect":"<p><span style=\"font-family: sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16.6667px;\">The psyker creates a small lame, </span></span><span style=\"font-family: sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16.6667px;\">approximately a centimetre across, at a point within </span></span><span style=\"font-family: sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16.6667px;\">range and line of sight. The lame is not large or hot </span></span><span style=\"font-family: sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16.6667px;\">enough to inlict damage, but can illuminate roughly </span></span><span style=\"font-family: sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16.6667px;\">a 5 metre radius. It can also ignite combustible </span></span><span style=\"font-family: sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16.6667px;\">materials at the GM&rsquo;s discretion, with the chance of </span></span><span style=\"font-family: sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16.6667px;\">igniting an object increasing the longer the psyker </span></span><span style=\"font-family: sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16.6667px;\">sustains the power. If the target of this power is a </span></span><span style=\"font-family: sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16.6667px;\">character, he must pass a Challenging (+0) Agility </span></span><span style=\"font-family: sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16.6667px;\">test each round the psyker sustains the power after </span></span><span style=\"font-family: sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16.6667px;\">the irst, or catch ire. The target gains a +30 bonus </span></span><span style=\"font-family: sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16.6667px;\">to this test on any round during which he performs </span></span><span style=\"font-family: sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16.6667px;\">an action with the Movement subtype.</span></span></p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/PsychicPowers/psychic-waves.svg","effects":[],"_id":"EvHkg5dBcfHd8ukN"}
{"name":"Impel","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>Developing psykers often instinctively exhibit rudimentary versions of the abilities shown in the disciplines of the Scholastica Psykana. Whereas an accomplished telekine can manipulate objects with more deftness than he could with his actual hands, an untrained psyker might simply lash out, shoving objects with blunt, yet effective, mental force.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"a rough telekine push","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Willpower 30","action":"Half","focusPower":{"difficulty":10,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"5*PR","sustained":"No","subtype":"Attack, Concentration","effect":"<p>The psyker chooses a target, which can be an object or character, and pushes it directly away from him a number of metres equal to his psy rating. To determine the maximum weight the psyker can push, consult the table on page 248 of the DARK HERESY Core Rulebook, substituting the psyker&rsquo;s PR and WPB for SB and TB. If the target is a character, he opposes the power with a Challenging (+0) Strength test. If the target fails with two or more degrees of failure, he is also knocked Prone. If the psyker wins by 3 or more degrees of success, the target sufers 1d5+PR damage and 1 level of Fatigue.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/PsychicPowers/psychic-waves.svg","effects":[],"_id":"FG6miJuTEiDZzVul"}
{"name":"Summon Vermin","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>Reaching out with his mind, the psyker calls out to nearby minor creatures, who unknowingly heed his summons.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"call out for small creatures","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Fellowship 30","action":"Full","focusPower":{"difficulty":0,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"1km*PR","sustained":"No","subtype":"Concentration","effect":"<p>A number of small animals&mdash;such as rats, snakes, and similar small creatures&mdash;up to the psyker&rsquo;s PR within range come to the psyker&rsquo;s current location as quickly as possible. The time until the creatures appear depends on their speed and proximity, and they are likely to arrive over the course of several rounds or minutes. Once the creatures arrive, they behave normally and are not compelled to obey the psyker.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/PsychicPowers/psychic-waves.svg","effects":[],"_id":"QhWB3lBUF25FBD2h"}
{"name":"Weapon Jinx","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>The psyker reaches out with his power, fouling the mechanisms of nearby weapons.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"fouling the mechanisms of nearby weapons.","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Intelligence 35","action":"Half","focusPower":{"difficulty":-10,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"5*PR","sustained":"No","subtype":"Concentration","effect":"<p>The psyker chooses a number of ranged weapons within range up to the psyker&rsquo;s psy rating, with each Best craftsmanship weapon counting as two weapons for the purposes of this power. Affected weapons count as Poor craftsmanship until repaired. If the psyker&rsquo;s degrees of success on the Focus Power test exceed the psy rating of the power, then the affected weapons also jam immediately. Should the psyker fail the test with 2 or more degrees of failure, his own ranged weapons jam immediately.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/PsychicPowers/psychic-waves.svg","effects":[],"_id":"YfoRlBhFJ0LMeXkQ"}
{"name":"Foretelling","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>Focussing his preternatural senses onto another person or object, the psyker receives a brief glimpse of the future.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"receive a brief and unclear image of the future","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Perception 35","action":"Full","focusPower":{"difficulty":-10,"test":"Psyniscience"},"range":"5*PR","sustained":"No","subtype":"Concentration","effect":"<p>The psyker chooses a single character or item within range and receives a brief and unclear image of the future, giving him a rough idea of one thing that will happen to the target within a number of minutes up to the psyker&rsquo;s PR. The GM decides what information the psyker receives, with additional degrees of success on the Focus Power test yielding more important information. For example, the psyker might learn that the character will be the target of an attack or will himself become violent, or that a cogitator will be accessed by an unknown individual. The psyker cannot select himself as the target of this power.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/PsychicPowers/psychic-waves.svg","effects":[],"_id":"bZUVm7Br8j2SWcDs"}
{"name":"Ill Omen","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>Drawing on Mankind&rsquo;s natural, and often quite justified, superstitious fears, the psyker bleeds just a miniscule drop of the Warp&rsquo;s inluence into the world. The result, while perhaps logically explainable, nonetheless instils a deep unease in those who witness it&mdash;an unmistakable sense of worse things to come. The exact nature of the omen could take any number of forms, including a raven crying three times, a small plant wilting, a disturbingly familiar patina of rust, animals spooking with no apparent cause, or anything else that might unnerve the target.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"give an omen to a target","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Rank 1 (Known) in the Psyniscience skill","action":"Full","focusPower":{"difficulty":-10,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"10*PR","sustained":"No","subtype":"Concentration","effect":"<p>The psyker chooses a single target within range and line of sight, who opposes this power with a Challenging (+0) Logic test. If the power is used during structured time and the target fails to resist, he sufers a &ndash;10 penalty to all tests for PR rounds. If used during narrative time, the psyker instead chooses a time within the next PR hours for the target to experience the omen. The GM determines the efects on the target&rsquo;s behaviour, but a likely result is that the target rethinks his current course of action or direction he is travelling. The GM should use the psyker&rsquo;s degrees of success and PR, as well as his suggestion for the form of the omen, in determining the outcome.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/PsychicPowers/psychic-waves.svg","effects":[],"_id":"cRprSZNf0vBVoin0"}
{"name":"Word of Beasts","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>Many untrained psykers, both in the wilds of feral worlds and the depths of hive cities, develop an instinctive ability to communicate with beasts and lower creatures. Whether this ability represents true telepathy or something else is impossible to say.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"\"communicate\" with animals","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Fellowship 35","action":"Half","focusPower":{"difficulty":-10,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"10","sustained":"No","subtype":"Concentration","effect":"<p>The psyker opens a limited telepathic link with an animal, which resists the power with a Challenging (+0) Willpower test. If the psyker succeeds, he chooses one of the following efects: <br />Impression Reading: The psyker receives a mental impression of the animal&rsquo;s recent experiences. These are not thoughts in the sense of a sentient being, but merely vague impressions and unclear images. The GM determines the level of detail and form of the information received based on the intelligence and senses of the animal, as well as the PR of the psyker. The amount of information is based on the psyker&rsquo;s degrees of success on the Focus Power test.</p>\n<p>Empathic Link: The psyker establishes a bond with the animal that persists after the telepathic link ends. The animal follows the psyker and obeys his commands to the best of its ability, exactly as if he had tamed and trained it with the Wrangling special use of the Survival skill (see page 116 of the DARK HERESY Core Rulebook).</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/PsychicPowers/psychic-waves.svg","effects":[],"_id":"fyj4Bciz4U56yTC7"}
{"name":"Deja Vu","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>The psyker reaches into his target&rsquo;s mind and momentarily scrambles synapses and memories, causing the target to relive his last few moments.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Target repeats the last action","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Willpower 35","action":"Half","focusPower":{"difficulty":-10,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"5*PR","sustained":"No","subtype":"Concentration","effect":"<p>The psyker selects a single target, who opposes the test with an Ordinary (+10) Willpower test. If the psyker succeeds, the target must repeat his last exploit, such as firing a gun at a target who is no longer there or diving for cover from a grenade that has already detonated. This repeated deed counts as the target&rsquo;s Action for the round. If the action would be obviously harmful to the target (but not to an ally), the target automatically wins the Opposed test (scoring 1 more degree of success than the psyker).</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/PsychicPowers/psychic-waves.svg","effects":[],"_id":"yMxLJ4XfhqxSJLzf"}
